<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="001" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Operator BU value setup + MCP verification</title>
    <phase>A.5: Operator BU value setup (Prerequisite)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1-2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>020, 021, 022, 023, 024, 025, 026, 027, 029, 050, 051, 071</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, operations, mcp, prerequisite</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Touches Dataverse production records via MCP; idempotent setup with explicit MCP verification gate. Not code implementation (no .cs/.ts/.tsx); not vague docs — has explicit constraints.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Prerequisite — must complete before Phase A wizards deploy</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Populate `businessunit.sprk_searchindexname` on the two known production BUs per design.md §5.0 and spec.md FR-OPS-01. This is a one-time operator setup that MUST complete BEFORE Phase A wizards deploy — wizards inherit empty strings otherwise. Verify each set via MCP query before marking complete.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke operator with Dataverse maker-portal access and MCP query familiarity. Read the field values from design.md §5.0 exactly — do not improvise.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `businessunit.sprk_searchindexname` set on Spaarke Demo BU = `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` and Spaarke BU = `spaarke-file-index`. MCP verification query returns those exact values. Spaarke Dev 1 and Spaarke Test 1 may remain NULL (operator-determined — design.md §5.0).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spaarke documents route to AI Search indexes via Business Unit. Spec FR-OPS-01 sets the two known BUs; without these values, the Phase A wizards (which cascade from BU at create time) write empty strings. This task is the prerequisite that unblocks Phase A.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/design.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-OPS-01">Spaarke Demo BU `sprk_searchindexname` = `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2`</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-OPS-01">Spaarke BU `sprk_searchindexname` = `spaarke-file-index`</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §5.0">Spaarke Dev 1 and Spaarke Test 1 may stay NULL — tenant default applies</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md INV-5">Never overwrite an existing non-null value — verify each BU is empty before setting</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MCP verification query is the gate that unblocks Phase A — do not mark complete without it</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="MCP read-then-write" location=".claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md">
        Read current value via `mcp__dataverse__read_query` BEFORE writing — confirms record exists and value is currently NULL (INV-5 honored).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Use MCP `mcp__dataverse__read_query` to list all Business Units with their current `sprk_searchindexname` value: `SELECT businessunitid, name, sprk_searchindexname FROM businessunit`.</step>
    <step order="2">Identify the businessunitid for Spaarke Demo BU and Spaarke BU. Confirm `sprk_searchindexname` is NULL on both (INV-5 — abort if non-null and flag for operator review).</step>
    <step order="3">Use MCP `mcp__dataverse__update_record` to set Spaarke Demo BU `sprk_searchindexname` = `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2`.</step>
    <step order="4">Use MCP `mcp__dataverse__update_record` to set Spaarke BU `sprk_searchindexname` = `spaarke-file-index`.</step>
    <step order="5">Re-run the read query from Step 1 to verify both values are set correctly. Capture the verification output to `projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/001-bu-setup-verification.md`.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `TASK-INDEX.md` status: 🔲 → ✅. Update `current-task.md` to reflect completion + advance to task 010 as next action.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Read BU records with current values</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__update_record">Update each BU's `sprk_searchindexname`</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="data">Dataverse: `businessunit` records updated (2 records)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/001-bu-setup-verification.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">MCP read-query of Spaarke Demo BU returns `sprk_searchindexname = "spaarke-knowledge-index-v2"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">MCP read-query of Spaarke BU returns `sprk_searchindexname = "spaarke-file-index"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">INV-5 honored — neither BU had a non-null value overwritten (verified by Step 2 read).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Verification file `notes/handoffs/001-bu-setup-verification.md` exists with MCP query output captured.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The two SPE container IDs corresponding to these indexes are documented in design.md §5.1. This task does NOT touch containers — only the AI Search index identifier on the BU. Phase A wizards will read these BU values via Xrm.WebApi at create time and cascade onto each new parent record.

    If the operator hasn't authorized MCP write access, fall back to the maker portal (Power Apps → Business Units → edit each BU's `sprk_searchindexname` field). Verification via MCP read remains the gate either way.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Before starting, load `spec.md` §FR-OPS-01 and `design.md` §5.0 for canonical values. Follow task-execute Step 0 (rigor declaration → STANDARD) before any MCP write.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
